article.description: Matt Stainbrook scored on a layup at the buzzer and finished with 18 points as Western Michigan edged Northern Illinois 82-80 Saturday.
article.headline: Northern Illinois falls short to Western Michigan
article.linkText: Northern Illinois falls short to Western Michigan
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- Matt Stainbrook scored on a layup at the buzzer and finished with 18 points as Western Michigan edged Northern Illinois 82-80 Saturday. Flenard Whitfield and Demetrius Ward each added 15 point for the Broncos (10-8, 3-2 Mid-American), who won their seventh straight at home. Xavier Silas led the Huskies (6-11, 2-3) with 23 points, and Tim Toler added 18. Down 80-76 with 28 seconds to play, Northern Illinois rallied to tie it on a free throw by Lee Fisher and Silas' 3-pointer with 16 seconds remaining. After Ward missed a layup in the closing seconds, Stainbrook grabbed the rebound and scored the winning basket. Western Michigan trailed by 14 in the first half and 40-34 at halftime before leading by nine in the second half.
